@node eplay "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Passage' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  The game consists of an area of various size and shape that
contains diagonal gates. Your position, indicated by a smiling face
icon, is located somewhere on the board. On some boards, walls as
well as blocks that are placed here and there, hinder your
movements and complicate the game a little...

  To play, click on the smiling face icon. You can only move
horizontally or vertically. Also, 3 obstacles and an empty space
must be around your position. These obstacles can be blocks, gates,
walls or one or more of the game board's borders. If the move is
possible, the smiling face icon will move towards the empty space.

  Gates have a diagonal shape, and so can only be moved diagonally.
Walls, if there are any, have small openings, so they can let gates
pass through. However, you cannot pass through these openings. An
'ascending' gate (which has a '/' shape) will move either to the
upper right or to the lower left. A 'descending' gate will move
toward the upper left or lower right. To move a gate, just click on
it and it will move, if there is an empty space (which can be the
exit tile) that is in line and next to the gate.

  On some game boards, several gates can be placed one after the
other in the same diagonal path. You may have to move some or even
all of them so you can move. Note that the exit may be partially
hidden by a gate.

  When you get to the exit (which is indicated by an 'E'), the game
board is completed and the game will display a new game board...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

